    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36.28"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <unclear reason="missing"/>
                        2-23-72 
                        <add>931 Cottonwood Dr.</add>
                    </dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute> 
                </opener>
                <p>For the record I'll put my request in writing. I've talked with Myrtle and Julius in regards to an interview with you for the American Field Service (<hi rend="caps">A.F.S.</hi>) students who are in the Lincoln high schools this year. All seniors, they are: 
                    <list>
                        <item><hi rend="caps">A.F.S.</hi> Student   Living with</item> 
                            <item>Chanjar Nakaret                   Dr. Rich'd Bradley
                                from Thailand                       East High 
                            Michael Stanic                          The Geo. Days
                                from Germany</item> 
                            
                        <item><hi rend="caps">A.F.S.</hi> Student   Living with</item>
                            <item>Asta Birkeland                    Dr. Henry Holtzclaws
                                from Norway                         Lincoln High 
                            Jurgeon Doring                          The Armin Kumms
                                from Germany</item> 
                            
                            <item>Rafael Ramirez                    The Kenneth Schmidts 
                                from Guatemala                      Northeast High</item>
                            
                            <item>Yasuko Okinaga                    The Max Hardings
                                from Japan                          Southeast High 
                            Johan Van Den Eynde                     The Chas. Umbergers</item>
                            
                            <item>Morten Ljosland                   The Howard Wiegers
                                from Norway                         Waverly High</item> 
                    </list>
                </p>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">28</fw> 
                <fw>1</fw>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36.28"/>
                
                <p>Because this is such a great opportunity to meet you the American brother or sister will, no doubt, accompany them if possible.</p>
                
                <p>These foreign students come for the school year and live in a family unit, as one of them, to become better acquainted with our American Culture.</p>
                
                <p>Some of our American students go to foreign countries on this some program as Americans Abroad.</p>
                
                <p>I think it would be a great privilege and experience for them to meet the great American in our midst &#8212; namely yourself, Dr. Neihardt.</p>
                
                <p>One of their requests is to be allowed to visit an Indian Reservation before they leave the States. I think a visit with you and a brief background of <hi rend="underline">Black Elk Speaks</hi> would heighten this desire. And our committee is working out arrangements to fulfuill their wish.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Hoping this interview can be arranged I am &#8212;</salute> <salute>Respectfully yours</salute> 
                
                    <signed>Norma Miller</signed> 
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">29</fw>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
